  "prompt": "Instagram (product): How do I quickly unfollow people on Instagram?",
  "response": "To quickly unfollow people on Instagram, you can use the following methods:\n\n### Using the Instagram App:\n1. **Open Instagram**: Launch the Instagram app on your mobile device.\n2. **Go to your Profile**: Tap on your profile icon located at the bottom right corner.\n3. **Tap on 'Following'**: You'll see a list of people you\u2019re following. Tap on 'Following' to view this list.\n4. **Unfollow**: Next to each person you follow, there should be a button that says 'Following.' Tap on this button, and then confirm that you want to unfollow by selecting 'Unfollow' from the pop-up menu.\n\n### Bulk Unfollow Method:\nTo unfollow multiple accounts at once, you could consider using a third-party app (make sure to research and choose a reputable one) or browse through your 'Following' list systematically while tapping unfollow.\n\n### Browser:\nYou can also access Instagram from a web browser:\n1. Go to the Instagram website and log in to your account.\n2. Click on your profile and select 'Following.'\n3. Click on 'Following' next to each account you want to unfollow, then confirm.\n\n### Note:\n- There is a limit to how many users you can unfollow in a day to prevent spammy behavior (usually around 200).\n- Be cautious with third-party tools, as they can violate Instagram's terms of service and potentially lead to account restrictions.\n\nFollowing these steps will help you manage who you follow on Instagram efficiently!",
